            vector addition or scalar multiplication.
            For example, 
            S\left( 2 {{S_valid_in}} \right) = {{S_valid_out_before}}
            but
            2S\left( {{S_valid_in}} \right) = {{S_valid_out_after}}

Show that T preserves both vector addition, since
T\left( {{xy}}+{{ab}}\right)=\cdots=
{{Tplus}}

T\left( {{xy}}\right)+T\left({{ab}}\right)=\cdots=
{{Tplus}}
are equal. Then show it also preserves
scalar multiplication, since
T\left( k{{xy}}\right)=
\cdots=
{{Ttimes}}

kT\left( {{xy}}\right)=\cdots=
{{Ttimes}}
are equal.
